            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "But this is works only when I don't have endpoint yet. If I alredy have `static` endpoint it will be terribly change one endpoint to another for all `url_for`. For example `url_for` have `_sheme` argument which change `url_addapter.url_sheme` forever for context: https://github.com/mitsuhiko/flask/commit/b5069d07a24a3c3a54fb056aa6f4076a0e7088c7.\n\nI can do somesthing similar:\n\n```\nreqctx = _request_ctx_stack.top\nurl_adapter = reqctx.url_adapter\nold_server_name = url_adapter.server_name\nurl_adapter.server_name = 'test.com'\nprint(url_for('static', filename='foobar.png', _external=True))\nurl_adapter.server_name = old_server_name\n```\n\nor\n\n```\nwith current_app.test_request_context('http://test.com'):\n    print(url_for('static', filename='test.png', _external=True))\n```\n\nBut it is not comfortably, especially in templates.\n"
